412 or Recodify Laws Regarding Residential Community Ownership Associations by
423 Adopting the Uniform Common Interest Ownership Act. The 12-member commission is
434 directed to review data on existing condominium and noncondominium community
445 ownership associations in the State, review state statutes that govern and case law that
456 affects condominium and noncondominium community ownership association
467 developments, review efforts in other states to address problems with community
478 ownership associations and consider the adoption of the Uniform Common Interest
489 Ownership Act. The commission is required to submit a report to the Joint Standing
590 Committee on Housing and Economic Development, which may submit legislation related
1501 to the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
